The paper deals with the problem of selecting an optimal sequence of coordinated behaviors in multi-robot systems for completing a given mission, which is a core problem in robotics. The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning based method for solving this problem, which involves Q-learning and online gradient descent. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which makes cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well.
